00:00:27,282 --> 00:00:29,182
Step right up,
boys and girls of all ages

6
00:00:29,183 --> 00:00:32,883
for the final act
of our big top extravaganza !

7
00:00:37,319 --> 00:00:39,144
Let's hear it one more time

8
00:00:39,177 --> 00:00:41,743
for Zelda, Queen of Knives !

9
00:00:42,181 --> 00:00:45,647
And now, City of Brotherly Love,

10
00:00:45,818 --> 00:00:48,518
birthplace of the American circus,

11
00:00:48,556 --> 00:00:50,522
let me introduce to you

12
00:00:50,524 --> 00:00:54,057
our headliner,
the Human Butterfly,

13
00:00:54,128 --> 00:00:58,028
Mia Romanov and her
magical metamorphosis !

14
00:01:58,609 --> 00:02:00,412
Well, boss, you wanted to see me ?

15
00:02:00,446 --> 00:02:02,047
Sit down.

16
00:02:09,655 --> 00:02:11,089
Moe kitchener.

17
00:02:12,023 --> 00:02:13,824
- What about him ?
- He got shot last night,

18
00:02:13,859 --> 00:02:15,660
outside a bar over in Roxborough.

19
00:02:17,629 --> 00:02:19,364
- You're serious ?
- Large caliber slug,

20
00:02:19,398 --> 00:02:20,632
Back of the head.

21
00:02:22,701 --> 00:02:25,237
So... he's dead ?

22
00:02:25,271 --> 00:02:27,205
Where were you last night, Lil ?

23
00:02:27,339 --> 00:02:30,074
Home. I was finishing up
a report.

24
00:02:30,109 --> 00:02:32,543
You're going to need
someone to confirm that.

25
00:02:33,112 --> 00:02:35,647
Who the investigating detective ?

26
00:02:36,614 --> 00:02:38,649
Doherty wants the state
police to handle it.

27
00:02:43,122 --> 00:02:44,622
They're gonna want to talk to you.

28
00:03:00,039 --> 00:03:01,506
You all right ?

29
00:03:02,041 --> 00:03:03,275
I don't know.

30
00:03:03,309 --> 00:03:04,442
Listen, I told the boss

31
00:03:04,477 --> 00:03:06,378
if anyone wants to know,
you were home when I

32
00:03:06,412 --> 00:03:07,879
dropped off that file last night.

33
00:03:07,913 --> 00:03:08,947
- The file...?
- Yeah.

34
00:03:08,981 --> 00:03:11,615
Rodriguez file, '06.

35
00:03:11,650 --> 00:03:14,351
No way you could've been across town
when Moe caught one

36
00:03:14,386 --> 00:03:15,686
outside that bar.

37
00:03:15,821 --> 00:03:17,089
Yeah.

38
00:03:18,523 --> 00:03:19,690
Thanks.

39
00:03:21,359 --> 00:03:23,862
Listen, I got a lady
waiting on a case.

40
00:03:24,196 --> 00:03:25,296
I'll handle it.

41
00:03:25,331 --> 00:03:26,932
I want to...

42
00:03:27,366 --> 00:03:28,833
keep working.

43
00:03:34,305 --> 00:03:36,942
Detectives Valens. Rush.

44
00:03:36,976 --> 00:03:38,510
You got something on an old

45
00:03:38,544 --> 00:03:40,111
Homicide, Miss Deluca ?

46
00:03:40,146 --> 00:03:41,379
Mia Romanov.

47
00:03:41,414 --> 00:03:43,614
An aerialist for the
Jones brothers circus.

48
00:03:43,649 --> 00:03:44,683
The circus ?

49
00:03:44,717 --> 00:03:46,718
Her death was ruled
an accidental fall

50
00:03:46,752 --> 00:03:48,019
in 1971.

51
00:03:48,054 --> 00:03:49,454
You're saying it wasn't ?

52
00:03:49,488 --> 00:03:50,722
Mia did a silk act where

53
00:03:50,756 --> 00:03:53,424
she came out of a cocoon
high above the rafters.

54
00:03:53,458 --> 00:03:56,260
I knew something was wrong
the moment she came out.

55
00:03:58,864 --> 00:04:00,064
This a bad time ?

56
00:04:00,499 --> 00:04:01,466
What ?

57
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:02,570
No.

58
00:04:03,771 --> 00:04:05,471
You were there
the night of her fall ?

59
00:04:05,705 --> 00:04:07,339
My mother worked
at Jones brothers circus.

60
00:04:07,573 --> 00:04:09,040
She was a fortune-teller.

61
00:04:09,275 --> 00:04:10,542
I'm a psychic.

62
00:04:10,576 --> 00:04:13,544
Always felt Mia's "accident"
was anything but.

63
00:04:13,578 --> 00:04:15,880
Then just tell us
who you "feel" killed her,

64
00:04:15,915 --> 00:04:17,782
and we'll clear this up
by lunchtime.

65
00:04:18,984 --> 00:04:20,318
Doesn't work that way.

66
00:04:20,352 --> 00:04:21,886
Yeah, it never does.

67
00:04:22,921 --> 00:04:24,489
Always wondered how
Mia could've fallen.

68
00:04:24,523 --> 00:04:26,891
And then I found
these at an exhibit,

69
00:04:26,925 --> 00:04:28,159
"Death under the big top."

70
00:04:28,193 --> 00:04:30,294
Photographs of various tragic falls,

71
00:04:30,295 --> 00:04:31,795
including Mia's.

72
00:04:31,796 --> 00:04:34,363
You can see how the other performers
braced for impact.

73
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:36,234
- Mia didn't.
- Fell head first.

74
00:04:36,268 --> 00:04:38,570
Arms limp, hands at her side.

75
00:04:38,604 --> 00:04:40,005
Might've been unconscious.

76
00:04:40,039 --> 00:04:41,206
Or already dead.

77
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:43,908
You think that her fall
was some kind of cover-up ?

78
00:04:43,943 --> 00:04:45,710
Mia grew up in the circus.

79
00:04:45,745 --> 00:04:47,245
Had the agility of a cat.

80
00:04:47,279 --> 00:04:48,680
Something wasn't right.

81
00:04:48,714 --> 00:04:49,781
I felt it.

82
00:04:49,815 --> 00:04:51,549
Yeah, we got that.

83
00:04:51,584 --> 00:04:53,451
We'll be in touch, Isabel.

84
00:04:54,886 --> 00:04:57,288
Your mother
will be fine.

85
00:04:59,992 --> 00:05:01,327
You...

86
00:05:01,728 --> 00:05:03,428
I'm not so sure.

87
00:05:08,867 --> 00:05:13,237
Cold Case
Season 7 Episode

88
00:05:35,034 --> 00:05:38,634
Metamorphosis

89
00:05:42,035 --> 00:05:43,468
Mia Romanov, 18.

90
00:05:43,503 --> 00:05:46,672
Died in St. Mary's fairgrounds
in '71, ruled accidental.

91
00:05:46,707 --> 00:05:47,873
More like inevitable.

92
00:05:47,908 --> 00:05:49,842
Flying through the air
on nothing but silk ?

93
00:05:49,876 --> 00:05:51,444
Not much here by the
way of statements.

94
00:05:51,478 --> 00:05:53,745
Well, getting circus
folk to talk isn't easy.

95
00:05:53,780 --> 00:05:55,881
Finally got warrants,
you're looking at an empty lot.

96
00:05:55,915 --> 00:05:57,849
Assigned spoke to a few
audience members.

97
00:05:57,918 --> 00:06:00,353
Said Mia looked fine
giving her pre-act bow.

98
00:06:00,387 --> 00:06:02,055
So whatever happened to her,
happened backstage.

99
00:06:02,089 --> 00:06:04,523
It's got the stink of
sabotage all over it.

100
00:06:04,557 --> 00:06:06,458
A/v blew up the
picture of Mia's fall.

101
00:06:06,492 --> 00:06:08,561
ME said the shadow around
her nose and mouth

102
00:06:08,562 --> 00:06:10,462
- could be blood.
- Before impact.

103
00:06:10,498 --> 00:06:13,131
Autopsy report : Broken neck,
shattered skull...

104
00:06:13,166 --> 00:06:14,366
Thought to have been
caused by the fall,

105
00:06:14,401 --> 00:06:17,069
but hands and wrists only
suffered minor damage.

106
00:06:17,103 --> 00:06:18,470
She didn't brace for impact.

107
00:06:18,505 --> 00:06:20,072
Survival instinct never kicked in.

108
00:06:20,106 --> 00:06:21,574
Run all the performers for priors,

109
00:06:21,608 --> 00:06:23,642
anything else we can
dig up on this big top.

110
00:06:24,277 --> 00:06:26,712
Mia was legally adopted
by Sheldon Burgess,

111
00:06:26,747 --> 00:06:28,480
aka Cleo the clown.

112
00:06:28,514 --> 00:06:29,514
Never gave a statement.

113
00:06:29,549 --> 00:06:31,416
Got an address over
in Point Breeze.

114
00:06:31,551 --> 00:06:32,985
Well, go talk to this clown.

115
00:06:43,296 --> 00:06:44,763
Mr. Burgess ?

116
00:06:45,598 --> 00:06:46,865
Welcome to Cleo's fun house.

117
00:06:46,899 --> 00:06:48,033
What can I do for you ?

118
00:06:48,068 --> 00:06:50,069
Homicide. We're looking

119
00:06:50,103 --> 00:06:52,137
into the death of Mia Romanov.

120
00:06:52,672 --> 00:06:53,973
Mia ?

121
00:06:55,342 --> 00:06:56,642
All these years later ?

122
00:06:56,676 --> 00:06:59,010
What can you tell us about her fall ?

123
00:06:59,045 --> 00:07:00,713
She was trying a new stunt.

124
00:07:03,016 --> 00:07:04,450
It's the worst night of my life.

125
00:07:04,484 --> 00:07:07,686
How come you didn't give
a statement, Mr. Burgess ?

126
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,656
I climbed deep into
a bottle that night.

127
00:07:10,690 --> 00:07:12,157
Stayed there for a long time after.

128
00:07:12,192 --> 00:07:14,760
It never crossed your mind that
maybe it wasn't an accident ?

129
00:07:14,794 --> 00:07:16,395
Silks weren't cut or frayed.

130
00:07:17,330 --> 00:07:18,864
Thought the moment
got the best of her.

131
00:07:18,899 --> 00:07:21,600
So who was in charge of
sending up her cocoon ?

132
00:07:21,634 --> 00:07:23,135
Gaucho, day players,
in and out.

133
00:07:23,170 --> 00:07:25,271
But Mia did her own rigging.

134
00:07:26,273 --> 00:07:28,374
She was stubborn, like her father.

135
00:07:28,408 --> 00:07:29,542
Her father ?

136
00:07:32,178 --> 00:07:34,180
The Romanovs have been
kicking the sawdust

137
00:07:34,214 --> 00:07:36,515
For five generations.

138
00:07:38,084 --> 00:07:40,486
They were royalty
amongst us kinkers.

139
00:07:40,520 --> 00:07:42,054
And mia was like her folks:

140
00:07:42,488 --> 00:07:45,023
More comfortable in the
air than on terra firma.

141
00:07:45,758 --> 00:07:48,059
How does a clown in
a traveling circus

142
00:07:48,094 --> 00:07:49,428
adopt a little girl ?

143
00:07:49,462 --> 00:07:50,996
I was her godfather.

144
00:07:51,030 --> 00:07:53,899
Her parents willed her to me,
but the circus raised her.

145
00:07:54,134 --> 00:07:56,770
Jones brothers was
a one-ring mud show,

146
00:07:56,771 --> 00:07:57,871
but we were family.

147
00:07:57,904 --> 00:08:00,072
- Anyone backstage with her ?
- The act before hers,

148
00:08:00,107 --> 00:08:02,475
Zelda "the queen of knives" panay.

149
00:08:02,709 --> 00:08:04,976
Zelda and Mia get on all right ?

150
00:08:05,011 --> 00:08:07,580
Oh, sure. Long as zelda
was the headliner.

151
00:08:09,816 --> 00:08:11,350
What the hell was that tonight ?

152
00:08:11,684 --> 00:08:14,019
Williamsport ?
Used to pack 'em to the stingers.

153
00:08:14,054 --> 00:08:15,989
Now, we're lucky to be making horse feed
out there.

154
00:08:15,990 --> 00:08:17,190
You still getting paid, Cleo ?

155
00:08:17,223 --> 00:08:19,224
This dog and pony
show is dying, Biggie.

156
00:08:19,358 --> 00:08:21,894
- We need an aerial act.
- Can't afford one.

157
00:08:21,961 --> 00:08:23,730
Unless you got one
in that wig of yours.

158
00:08:23,731 --> 00:08:25,631
No way a knife-thrower
can carry the big top.

159
00:08:25,664 --> 00:08:27,132
- Excuse me ?
- No offense, zelda.

160
00:08:27,167 --> 00:08:28,134
- I've been...
- Stop it.

161
00:08:28,168 --> 00:08:30,603
Everybody, please, just...

162
00:08:32,105 --> 00:08:34,740
I ca... I can give
us an aerial act.

163
00:08:35,074 --> 00:08:36,375
Mia, I didn't mean you should...

164
00:08:36,409 --> 00:08:37,376
I can fly.

165
00:08:37,410 --> 00:08:38,744
It's in my blood.

166
00:08:39,478 --> 00:08:40,646
She's a baby.

167
00:08:40,780 --> 00:08:42,347
Well, what do we got to lose?

168
00:08:42,382 --> 00:08:44,383
Even a baby can see we're dying.

169
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:48,888
I'll talk to management.

170
00:08:48,922 --> 00:08:50,523
Start putting it together, kid.

171
00:08:51,957 --> 00:08:54,760
- I don't know, Mia.
- It's going to be fine, cleo.

172
00:09:01,467 --> 00:09:03,202
Accidents happen.

173
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:10,108
Zelda P-A-N-A-Y...

174
00:09:10,443 --> 00:09:11,610
Was the headliner prior to Mia ?

175
00:09:11,645 --> 00:09:13,612
Yeah, ever since the
last aerial act walked.

176
00:09:13,646 --> 00:09:15,647
I didn't want Mia up there.

177
00:09:15,881 --> 00:09:18,384
Hate to think I put
a target on her.

178
00:09:18,418 --> 00:09:21,286
Sounds like zelda wasn't
ready to put her knives away.

179
00:09:25,291 --> 00:09:27,059
- Thanks for coming in.
- Well, if I'd known

180
00:09:27,093 --> 00:09:28,360
you were so handsome,

181
00:09:28,394 --> 00:09:31,563
I would've sprinted
all the way from Atlantic City.

182
00:09:32,097 --> 00:09:34,298
I don't mean to be rude,

183
00:09:34,332 --> 00:09:36,400
but can we get going on this,

184
00:09:36,635 --> 00:09:38,637
because... I got a show, at 6:00.

185
00:09:38,771 --> 00:09:40,439
- Still performing ?
- Yeah, well, it's mostly

186
00:09:40,473 --> 00:09:42,474
blue plate dinners for seniors.

187
00:09:42,509 --> 00:09:45,678
But they remember me from
the Ed Sullivan Show.

188
00:09:45,712 --> 00:09:48,079
How did you and Mia
romanov get along ?

189
00:09:48,514 --> 00:09:50,115
Mia Romanov ?

190
00:09:51,984 --> 00:09:53,285
Fine.

191
00:09:53,319 --> 00:09:54,787
I took her under my wing.

192
00:09:54,821 --> 00:09:56,488
She was like my sister.

193
00:09:56,523 --> 00:09:58,657
You always throw daggers
at family ?

194
00:09:59,391 --> 00:10:00,693
Darling...

195
00:10:01,627 --> 00:10:04,462
even a lady loses
her cool sometimes,

196
00:10:04,497 --> 00:10:07,800
Which accounts for three
out of four of my divorces.

197
00:10:07,934 --> 00:10:10,335
Foolish. Jealous.

198
00:10:10,469 --> 00:10:12,103
Jealous enough to get rid of her ?

199
00:10:12,138 --> 00:10:13,472
What do you mean ?

200
00:10:14,106 --> 00:10:15,341
She fell.

201
00:10:16,175 --> 00:10:17,542
I was there.

202
00:10:17,577 --> 00:10:19,745
With her backstage before her act.

203
00:10:19,779 --> 00:10:21,580
Your "sister" ends up dead

204
00:10:21,614 --> 00:10:23,582
And you get to keep your spotlight.

205
00:10:23,616 --> 00:10:25,417
Now, I got my pride.

206
00:10:26,051 --> 00:10:27,920
But I'm not stupid.

207
00:10:28,254 --> 00:10:30,088
We needed mia's act to work.

208
00:10:30,123 --> 00:10:33,258
It was all over, for all of us.

209
00:10:35,562 --> 00:10:39,598
<i>"Waiting for the sun"
by The Doors.</i>

210
00:10:40,333 --> 00:10:43,134
- Where's the trapeze bar ?
- Forget the trapeze.

211
00:10:44,169 --> 00:10:46,371
Biggie, we need something new.
We need dramatic.

212
00:10:46,406 --> 00:10:47,339
You'll never be ready in a week

213
00:10:47,374 --> 00:10:48,607
Trying to get a new act together.

214
00:10:48,642 --> 00:10:50,009
Just do what your folks taught you.

215
00:10:50,043 --> 00:10:51,610
I need a theme.

216
00:10:51,844 --> 00:10:53,078
To tell a story.

217
00:10:53,112 --> 00:10:55,381
- I need some time.
- You're not a clown anymore.

218
00:10:55,415 --> 00:10:58,149
It's not about stories.
It's about wowing them.

219
00:10:58,184 --> 00:10:59,785
Yeah, that's what I'm trying to do.
There's something

220
00:10:59,819 --> 00:11:01,720
Groovy with the silks-
the freedom it gives me...

221
00:11:01,755 --> 00:11:02,821
People don't want groovy.

222
00:11:02,856 --> 00:11:04,356
They want tradition.

223
00:11:04,390 --> 00:11:06,592
For their kids to see
and feel what they did.

224
00:11:06,626 --> 00:11:08,294
Maybe we can start a new one.

225
00:11:08,328 --> 00:11:10,696
You know, we can capture
their imagination. Great.

226
00:11:10,730 --> 00:11:13,731
Then imagine there's no
circus when we get shut down

227
00:11:13,766 --> 00:11:15,467
waiting for you to get
your act together.

228
00:11:15,501 --> 00:11:17,001
Now this is all on me ?

229
00:11:17,036 --> 00:11:19,471
You asked for a shot, kid,
and I gave it to you.

230
00:11:19,506 --> 00:11:21,140
Convinced management
to roll the dice.

231
00:11:21,174 --> 00:11:24,043
- Don't hang me out to dry.
- No, I'll do the silk act.

232
00:11:24,077 --> 00:11:25,644
I'll use a mechanic if I have to.
The advance men

233
00:11:25,679 --> 00:11:27,746
have been pumping your
act as death-defying.

234
00:11:27,781 --> 00:11:29,214
- But I...
- But nothing !

235
00:11:30,316 --> 00:11:32,318
I took a flyer on you.

236
00:11:32,352 --> 00:11:35,721
You'd better not make a fool of me.

237
00:11:41,861 --> 00:11:45,431
Mia was way ahead of the curve.

238
00:11:45,465 --> 00:11:48,967
She was cirque du
soleil before they were.

239
00:11:49,002 --> 00:11:51,904
Now everybody's got a silk act.

240
00:11:51,938 --> 00:11:53,639
What about David and Goliath ?

241
00:11:53,673 --> 00:11:55,908
Ringmaster Biggie Jones
and his goon,

242
00:11:55,942 --> 00:11:58,710
Lester "Gargantuan" Smith.

243
00:11:59,812 --> 00:12:01,380
Biggie pushed us hard.

244
00:12:01,414 --> 00:12:04,483
Maybe pushed Mia too hard.

245
00:12:05,217 --> 00:12:07,919
That's probably why he
pulled up stakes so fast

246
00:12:07,953 --> 00:12:09,387
and left town that night.

247
00:12:10,090 --> 00:12:13,159
You see Biggie backstage
with Mia before her fall ?

248
00:12:13,193 --> 00:12:16,428
Biggie always checked
on the featured acts

249
00:12:16,863 --> 00:12:18,597
before they went on.

250
00:12:20,766 --> 00:12:22,801
Have information that you called in

251
00:12:22,836 --> 00:12:24,470
the 10-37 last week.

252
00:12:24,505 --> 00:12:27,172
DUI check on Mr. Kitchener ?

253
00:12:27,407 --> 00:12:28,707
That's right.

254
00:12:28,741 --> 00:12:30,709
Outside the same bar
that he was murdered ?

255
00:12:30,743 --> 00:12:33,912
- The suspect was inebriated.
- Suspect was awaiting trial.

256
00:12:34,346 --> 00:12:36,248
And what were you doing
observing him in the first place ?

257
00:12:36,282 --> 00:12:37,983
It was a continuing investigation.

258
00:12:38,017 --> 00:12:40,452
He had already filed a
complaint against you.

259
00:12:40,486 --> 00:12:42,088
Which was completely bogus,

