Destroying Mia's rig,

531
00:26:07,612 --> 00:26:08,745
Threatening her in front of
witnesses...

532
00:26:08,779 --> 00:26:10,213
- those aren't mistakes ?
- Wait a second.

533
00:26:10,248 --> 00:26:11,515
I didn't even work the big top.

534
00:26:11,549 --> 00:26:12,782
I know. She had you kicked out.

535
00:26:12,817 --> 00:26:14,984
Had you shoveling pachyderm pies.

536
00:26:15,019 --> 00:26:17,220
Cost you money,
not to mention your pride.

537
00:26:17,255 --> 00:26:18,321
About to narc you out.

538
00:26:18,356 --> 00:26:20,156
But you weren't looking
to do jail time,

539
00:26:20,191 --> 00:26:21,892
- so you did her instead.
- You got me.

540
00:26:21,926 --> 00:26:23,593
Guilty as charged.

541
00:26:24,695 --> 00:26:26,563
If you call love a crime.

542
00:26:26,597 --> 00:26:27,764
Love ?

543
00:26:27,799 --> 00:26:29,733
Anyone could see that that girl

544
00:26:29,767 --> 00:26:31,601
was a bud about to bloom.

545
00:26:31,636 --> 00:26:32,602
All she needed was

546
00:26:32,637 --> 00:26:33,803
a double dose of Eddie.

547
00:26:33,838 --> 00:26:35,772
I might just hit you on principle.

548
00:26:35,806 --> 00:26:38,174
Seem to have that effect on women.

549
00:26:38,209 --> 00:26:40,210
The other side of desire.

550
00:26:41,044 --> 00:26:44,347
That young lady
was bursting with it.

551
00:26:48,652 --> 00:26:52,692
<i>"Riders on the storm"
by The Doors.</i>

552
00:26:57,895 --> 00:26:59,896
Hey, I'm sorry about yesterday.

553
00:27:00,430 --> 00:27:02,565
I've been shoveling
crap my whole life.

554
00:27:02,999 --> 00:27:05,402
So don't lose
any sleep over me, okay ?

555
00:27:07,037 --> 00:27:08,471
I'm just under a lot of pressure

556
00:27:08,505 --> 00:27:11,675
and I could've handled it better.

557
00:27:14,010 --> 00:27:15,711
I heard about your folks.

558
00:27:16,414 --> 00:27:18,315
It takes a lot of guts
doing what you're doing.

559
00:27:19,684 --> 00:27:21,585
Well, I don't really
know what else to do.

560
00:27:21,619 --> 00:27:24,621
I mean... family needs me.

561
00:27:24,655 --> 00:27:27,090
I guess you had to grow up
a little fast around here.

562
00:27:27,124 --> 00:27:30,827
So maybe, you and I aren't
so different after all.

563
00:27:31,762 --> 00:27:33,530
Sounds like you've been around
quite a bit. What about you ?

564
00:27:33,565 --> 00:27:36,266
I never heard of a circus
that didn't travel.

565
00:27:36,300 --> 00:27:37,967
I've been to a bunch of places,

566
00:27:38,002 --> 00:27:39,970
but I never get to leave the lot.

567
00:27:40,004 --> 00:27:41,572
Never ?

568
00:27:42,707 --> 00:27:44,741
Once.

569
00:27:45,176 --> 00:27:46,576
When I was a little girl,

570
00:27:46,611 --> 00:27:48,912
my mom took me down
to bourbon street.

571
00:27:48,946 --> 00:27:50,547
New Orleans.

572
00:27:50,581 --> 00:27:53,183
There was one of
those jazz funerals.

573
00:27:54,285 --> 00:27:56,487
Something eerie about it, but...

574
00:27:57,921 --> 00:27:59,522
It was beautiful.

575
00:28:09,367 --> 00:28:11,134
We should go out tonight.

576
00:28:12,503 --> 00:28:14,938
I'm not sure cleo would like that.

577
00:28:15,572 --> 00:28:18,975
Not all adventures are out there.

578
00:29:11,195 --> 00:29:12,896
You should come with me.

579
00:29:15,165 --> 00:29:16,834
Where ?

580
00:29:17,868 --> 00:29:20,303
Anywhere but this
stick and rag show.

581
00:29:23,140 --> 00:29:24,407
You're 18.

582
00:29:24,442 --> 00:29:26,543
- You can do anything you want.
- Mia !

583
00:29:26,577 --> 00:29:28,044
Giving it up to some gaucho !

584
00:29:28,079 --> 00:29:29,412
Have you lost your mind ?!

585
00:29:29,447 --> 00:29:30,547
- Come on !
- No !

586
00:29:30,581 --> 00:29:32,215
- Get out. Come with me !
- Wait...

587
00:29:32,249 --> 00:29:34,250
Cleo ! No !

588
00:29:34,285 --> 00:29:35,919
Come on !

589
00:29:41,659 --> 00:29:43,326
I felt bad for Mia.

590
00:29:43,360 --> 00:29:44,760
If you ask me, there was something

591
00:29:44,795 --> 00:29:46,796
weird was going on
between those two.

592
00:29:46,830 --> 00:29:49,933
You know, she was 18 and they
were still sharing a boxcar.

593
00:29:49,967 --> 00:29:51,167
- Sketchy.
- Sketchier

594
00:29:51,202 --> 00:29:53,369
- than an alcoholic clown ?
- Next day,

595
00:29:53,404 --> 00:29:55,071
She had a busted lip,

596
00:29:55,406 --> 00:29:57,107
Compliments of Cleo.

597
00:29:57,741 --> 00:29:59,943
You painted a pretty
picture of mia, cleo.

598
00:30:00,677 --> 00:30:03,379
But, uh, but she wasn't
such an angel, now, was she ?

599
00:30:03,613 --> 00:30:06,549
Droppin' acid, doing riggers...

600
00:30:06,683 --> 00:30:07,650
Then there's you.

601
00:30:07,685 --> 00:30:09,385
Me ?! What the hell's
that supposed to mean ?

602
00:30:09,420 --> 00:30:11,321
Keeping tight quarters
with a teenage girl

603
00:30:11,355 --> 00:30:13,523
All those years...
Used to having her

604
00:30:13,557 --> 00:30:15,425
- by your side.
- What are you saying ?

605
00:30:15,459 --> 00:30:17,227
Take a seat.

606
00:30:19,229 --> 00:30:21,064
I slept on the floor.

607
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:24,334
I would never, ever do

608
00:30:24,368 --> 00:30:25,468
what you're suggesting.

609
00:30:25,503 --> 00:30:27,437
Mia was my daughter.
She was not blood.

610
00:30:27,471 --> 00:30:29,038
Was to me !

611
00:30:29,073 --> 00:30:30,907
Maybe I was strict
and overprotective,

612
00:30:30,941 --> 00:30:32,976
but that place was
swarming with snakes.

613
00:30:33,010 --> 00:30:34,077
Like Eddie Armstrong ?

614
00:30:34,111 --> 00:30:36,412
Damn straight.

615
00:30:36,447 --> 00:30:39,749
Combed the lot,
found her tripping with that...

616
00:30:39,784 --> 00:30:41,684
fink trying to get in her pants.

617
00:30:41,719 --> 00:30:42,886
I just snapped.

618
00:30:42,920 --> 00:30:44,988
Oh, busted her lip trying
to show her who's boss.

619
00:30:45,022 --> 00:30:46,224
No !

620
00:30:46,525 --> 00:30:48,225
Never laid a hand on her.

621
00:30:49,160 --> 00:30:50,760
She was so out of it, kept falling.

622
00:30:50,795 --> 00:30:53,462
I watched her all
night till she finally

623
00:30:53,497 --> 00:30:55,231
- Came down.
- Always there to catch her, huh ?

624
00:30:56,600 --> 00:30:59,335
Not always.

625
00:30:59,370 --> 00:31:01,938
But I tried.

626
00:31:01,972 --> 00:31:03,573
But you couldn't let go.

627
00:31:03,607 --> 00:31:04,841
And all you had was her

628
00:31:04,875 --> 00:31:06,442
and that bottle.

629
00:31:06,477 --> 00:31:07,644
She was becoming a woman.

630
00:31:07,678 --> 00:31:08,812
You were losing her.

631
00:31:08,846 --> 00:31:10,346
Holding her back so much that...

632
00:31:10,381 --> 00:31:12,282
You were suffocating her.

633
00:31:12,316 --> 00:31:13,249
No, you're wrong.

634
00:31:13,284 --> 00:31:15,652
Loved her so much,
I wanted her to go.

635
00:31:15,686 --> 00:31:18,688
She needed to get
away from that place.

636
00:31:19,890 --> 00:31:21,291
From me.

637
00:31:25,662 --> 00:31:29,731
<i>"Moonlight drive" by The Doors.</i>

638
00:32:53,450 --> 00:32:56,653
<i>For Mia Romanov and her amazing</i>

639
00:32:56,687 --> 00:32:57,854
<i>metamorphosis !</i>

640
00:33:00,088 --> 00:33:01,590
You were...

641
00:33:02,625 --> 00:33:03,826
beautiful !

642
00:33:03,860 --> 00:33:05,361
You looked just like
your mother up there.

643
00:33:06,196 --> 00:33:07,929
- You liked it ?
- I've seen the future,

644
00:33:07,964 --> 00:33:09,165
and you're it, kiddo.

645
00:33:09,199 --> 00:33:10,700
Your act is too good for this top.

646
00:33:10,734 --> 00:33:13,336
What are you talking about?
This is exactly what we need.

647
00:33:13,370 --> 00:33:15,738
You heard the crowd. This will save us.
This place is dying.

648
00:33:15,773 --> 00:33:17,273
You don't need to die with it.

649
00:33:17,907 --> 00:33:19,309
But this is my family.

650
00:33:19,343 --> 00:33:21,044
Cleo, I'm not going anywhere.

651
00:33:21,078 --> 00:33:22,648
You know how...

652
00:33:23,149 --> 00:33:25,349
when a circus elephant is born,

653
00:33:25,382 --> 00:33:28,551
the bull handler will
secure it with a thin rope

654
00:33:28,585 --> 00:33:30,753
Tied to a skinny
stick in the ground?

655
00:33:30,788 --> 00:33:32,789
Sure, and when that
elephant grows up,

656
00:33:32,823 --> 00:33:36,893
that rope and skinny stick
can still make him stay put.

657
00:33:36,927 --> 00:33:41,464
That stick can't hold you anymore.

658
00:33:41,498 --> 00:33:43,666
Are you calling me an elephant?

659
00:33:49,873 --> 00:33:53,443
I wish she'd listened to me,
but it was already too late.

660
00:33:53,577 --> 00:33:54,911
She fell the next night.

661
00:33:55,046 --> 00:33:56,980
Buried her in the Romanov family plot.

662
00:33:57,714 --> 00:34:00,449
A few days later, I was back
on the sawdust in Allentown.

663
00:34:00,684 --> 00:34:02,218
A few days?

664
00:34:02,652 --> 00:34:04,554
Thought the circus
Was due in allentown

665
00:34:04,588 --> 00:34:06,122
The night after the accident?

666
00:34:06,156 --> 00:34:07,357
Don't know who told you that.

667
00:34:07,391 --> 00:34:09,292
No, we had a week between stops.

668
00:34:09,826 --> 00:34:11,661
Got the route card to prove it.

669
00:34:17,001 --> 00:34:18,970
Losing track of all
your lies, Biggie.

670
00:34:19,304 --> 00:34:21,172
Told us you were due
in Allentown

671
00:34:21,206 --> 00:34:23,140
when you had a week between gigs.

672
00:34:23,175 --> 00:34:26,977
We had to wildcat it out of
there after Mia's nosedive.

673
00:34:27,012 --> 00:34:29,046
Especially since you had a
murder scene to tear down.

674
00:34:30,381 --> 00:34:31,882
Come on, who's going
to take their kiddies

675
00:34:31,916 --> 00:34:34,084
to see us after a fall like that ?

676
00:34:34,118 --> 00:34:35,619
Thought with a little
extra time,

677
00:34:35,653 --> 00:34:37,455
we could drum up some business
in Allentown.

678
00:34:40,158 --> 00:34:41,125
I know what it looks like,

679
00:34:41,159 --> 00:34:43,727
- but it was a business decision.
- You weren't the only one

680
00:34:43,761 --> 00:34:44,962
Making business decisions.

681
00:34:44,996 --> 00:34:47,131
Found out Ringling
Brothers wanted Mia.

682
00:34:47,265 --> 00:34:50,233
Ringling-- they tried
to poach everyone.

683
00:34:50,268 --> 00:34:52,736
After everything your
family had done for her.

684
00:34:52,770 --> 00:34:54,271
Raising Mia as one of their own.

685
00:34:54,306 --> 00:34:56,239
Knew if you lost her,
it was all over.

686
00:34:56,274 --> 00:34:57,574
But Mia wouldn't fall in line.

687
00:34:57,609 --> 00:35:00,043
Left a little man with a
big temper holding the bag.

688
00:35:00,077 --> 00:35:01,345
And when it's all said and done,

689
00:35:02,180 --> 00:35:03,981
Mia ends up eating sawdust.

690
00:35:04,015 --> 00:35:05,216
Come on, you guys.

691
00:35:06,951 --> 00:35:08,786
Do I look like I could hurt anyone ?

692
00:35:09,620 --> 00:35:11,354
Spoke to Biggie, Lester.

693
00:35:11,688 --> 00:35:13,456
Remember him ?

694
00:35:13,490 --> 00:35:15,458
Yes. Biggie.

695
00:35:15,493 --> 00:35:18,494
Well, he says you killed Mia.

696
00:35:18,829 --> 00:35:19,997
Me ?

697
00:35:20,131 --> 00:35:21,465
Biggie couldn't have killed Mia.

698
00:35:21,599 --> 00:35:24,100
Couldn't have lifted her
up into that cocoon.

699
00:35:24,835 --> 00:35:28,304
I'm thinking he
forced you to do it, Lester.

700
00:35:28,338 --> 00:35:31,207
Like he always forced you.

701
00:35:31,843 --> 00:35:33,544
You don't have to be scared
of Biggie anymore.

702
00:35:33,578 --> 00:35:35,212
He can't hurt you.

703
00:35:35,547 --> 00:35:37,047
No, you got it wrong !

704
00:35:37,081 --> 00:35:39,783
You put yourself
At the scene, Biggie.

705
00:35:40,217 --> 00:35:41,584
Said she was "good to go."

706
00:35:41,619 --> 00:35:44,221
Mia was dead. You got Lester
to stuff her into silks just

707
00:35:44,255 --> 00:35:46,124
- to cover it up.
- I'd done

708
00:35:46,126 --> 00:35:47,695
some things I had to do.

709
00:35:48,696 --> 00:35:51,496
But I did not kill Mia.

710
00:35:54,866 --> 00:35:56,667
<i>If you could please find
it in your heart to donate</i>

711
00:35:56,701 --> 00:35:58,468
<i>again to help orphaned
children get a chance</i>

712
00:35:58,503 --> 00:35:59,736
<i>to see the human butterfly.</i>

713
00:35:59,771 --> 00:36:02,138
<i>In return, for helping make
these children's dreams come true,</i>

714
00:36:02,172 --> 00:36:04,575
<i>your company</i>
name will be featured
in our special program.

715
00:36:04,609 --> 00:36:06,243
Hey, Mia.

716
00:36:07,412 --> 00:36:09,846
- What are you doing here ?
- This makes no sense.

717
00:36:09,881 --> 00:36:11,114
It says we've sold 800 tickets.

718
00:36:11,149 --> 00:36:12,282
The top only sits 400.

719
00:36:12,317 --> 00:36:13,917
- What are you doing, Biggie ?
- All right, everyone.

720
00:36:13,952 --> 00:36:15,719
Scram.

721
00:36:17,087 --> 00:36:18,956
Listen, sweetheart,

722
00:36:18,990 --> 00:36:21,825
to make sure that
the show can go on,

723
00:36:21,859 --> 00:36:23,661
- I've had to be a little creative.
- We're not affiliated

724
00:36:23,662 --> 00:36:26,296
with any charity, but you're selling
tickets in their name.

725
00:36:26,531 --> 00:36:28,165
Where were these kids
in the stands ?

726
00:36:28,199 --> 00:36:30,133
It's a write-off to
local businesses.

727
00:36:30,168 --> 00:36:32,135
It's one thing to rip
people off on the midway,

728
00:36:32,170 --> 00:36:34,072
But you're going to use my act
to scam

729
00:36:34,073 --> 00:36:36,240
- charities for orphans ?
- What do you care ?

730
00:36:36,274 --> 00:36:38,775
You'll be flying under
the ringling top soon.

731
00:36:39,909 --> 00:36:40,644
What ?

732
00:36:40,679 --> 00:36:42,946
That's right. I know all about it.

733
00:36:44,816 --> 00:36:46,650
I can't believe you, Biggie.

734
00:36:47,819 --> 00:36:50,420
I was going to tell them "no.
" but now?

735
00:37:01,098 --> 00:37:02,966
Once I told management,

736
00:37:03,001 --> 00:37:04,801
it was out of my hands.

737
00:37:04,836 --> 00:37:05,802
Management, huh ?

738
00:37:05,837 --> 00:37:07,604
Controlled the whole thing.

739
00:37:07,639 --> 00:37:09,439
And just who was
this management ?

740
00:37:10,642 --> 00:37:13,310
- Bunch of suits out of florida.
- You see, that's a crock.

741
00:37:13,344 --> 00:37:15,312
The SEC has no record

742
00:37:15,346 --> 00:37:17,280
of J.B. Ricketts investments.

743
00:37:17,315 --> 00:37:18,649
But Wikipedia does.

744
00:37:19,283 --> 00:37:20,851
J.B. Ricketts founded

745
00:37:20,885 --> 00:37:22,486
the American circus.

746
00:37:23,320 --> 00:37:25,088
Died in 1799.

747
00:37:25,923 --> 00:37:27,323
There was no management.

748
00:37:27,358 --> 00:37:29,159
It was you. No.

749
00:37:30,495 --> 00:37:32,629
If it were just that simple.

750
00:37:33,798 --> 00:37:36,533
You were diagnosed with

751
00:37:36,567 --> 00:37:40,003
is it cerebral gigantism ?

752
00:37:40,038 --> 00:37:41,738
It's a pretty rare disorder.

753
00:37:41,773 --> 00:37:44,374
Often accompanied with diminished

754
00:37:44,409 --> 00:37:45,876
Mental capacity.

755
00:37:45,910 --> 00:37:47,611
The d.A.'s willing to
cut a deal for you.

756
00:37:47,645 --> 00:37:49,246
We don't want to
send you to county,

757
00:37:49,280 --> 00:37:50,447
so you tell us what happened

758
00:37:50,481 --> 00:37:51,982
and we'll make sure you go

759
00:37:52,016 --> 00:37:53,350
to a comfortable medical facility.

760
00:37:53,384 --> 00:37:55,585
Oh, yeah, they'll get
you squared away.

761
00:37:55,620 --> 00:37:59,122
In a year or two, you're a
handyman in Reading again.

762
00:38:01,326 --> 00:38:03,460
Help us put biggie away for good.

763
00:38:13,170 --> 00:38:16,907
Biggie was a... a monster.

764
00:38:17,508 --> 00:38:18,709
He...

765
00:38:19,043 --> 00:38:20,213
he...

766
00:38:21,214 --> 00:38:23,314
he made me.

767
00:38:25,917 --> 00:38:28,018
This lifeline,

768
00:38:28,052 --> 00:38:29,419
Those meds--

769
00:38:29,454 --> 00:38:30,954
Pretty expensive. I didn't know

770
00:38:30,988 --> 00:38:32,522
The circus had such great benefits.

771
00:38:32,557 --> 00:38:34,524
So, we decided to check.

772
00:38:34,559 --> 00:38:35,759
Turns out they don't.

773
00:38:35,993 --> 00:38:38,295
Your medicine is paid for
by a private company.

774
00:38:38,329 --> 00:38:39,830
Same company pays your rent.

775
00:38:40,798 --> 00:38:42,999
- You don't get it, do you ?
- No, I get it.

776
00:38:43,034 --> 00:38:45,402
And you're going to prison,
and there's no ppo in the pokie.

777
00:38:45,436 --> 00:38:48,071
A guy like you won't
last six months.

778
00:38:50,141 --> 00:38:51,341
Last time, big.

779
00:38:51,375 --> 00:38:52,642
Who was management ?

780
00:38:58,649 --> 00:39:01,118
"he made me."

781
00:39:01,252 --> 00:39:03,286
Man, I hope we got that on video.

782
00:39:03,321 --> 00:39:05,288
Submit it to the academy.

783
00:39:05,322 --> 00:39:07,991
See, the thing is,
people with cerebral gigantism,

784
00:39:08,025 --> 00:39:09,893
Although usually
bigger as children,

785
00:39:09,927 --> 00:39:12,195
Are often in the normal
height range as adults.

786
00:39:12,230 --> 00:39:13,830
Far from normal, gargantuan.

787
00:39:13,865 --> 00:39:16,032
That country doctor
misdiagnosed you.

788
00:39:16,067 --> 00:39:17,968
